AGI - A reminese 27-year-old was arrested and taken to prison on the charge of segregated and beaten his partner and wounded, sending her to the hospital, their 18-month-old daughter. The man, defended by lawyer Gilberto Martinini, is currently held after being arrested by the Carabinieri in early February. The judge for the preliminary investigations of Rimini has placed the immediate judgment for mistreatment and injury, fixing the hearing on 15 May next. According to the reconstruction of the pollutants, the child would be relieved of weight, slammed on the bed and hit repeatedly >, bringing back a cranial and cervical trauma judged healable in seven days. The episode dates back to a week before the man's arrest.
The investigations brought out a long series of abuses and harassment against women and their daughter. Between 3 and 5 February, the mother and the child would be held prisoner in a room of a residence in Riccione. The man would have locked them, preventing them from leaving. At the height of a wrath access, he would have destroyed the television, launched an iron bowl against his partner and broken his cell phone to prevent her from asking for help. Branding a pair of scissors, he would then threaten to kill both the woman and the child.
The woman, as the local newspapers report, managed to escape taking advantage of a time when the man had fallen asleep. With the child in his arm, he found refuge in a Dante street shop, where the trader hid it and called the carabinieri. The 27-year-old, awake and aware of the escape, launched from the residence's balcony and tried to enter the store by force, but was blocked and arrested by the military shortly after.&nbsp;

